Question: Explain to a younger friend how to apply for a college.
Answer:
Applying for a college is a difficult and interesting task, you can learn a lot from the process. First, you need to do selection from hundreds of universities, not the higher ranking one, but the fit one. Then submit your information online, which contains personal description, three recommend letters and your grading copies. Finally, contact with the professor you want to work with by sending an email, which will be better to know more about your work and your research environment.